article.headline: Fresno St. 74, Winston-Salem 64
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) -- Eddie Miller scored 25 points with seven 3-pointers and Fresno State rallied from a 10-point first-half deficit to beat Winston-Salem State 74-64 on Tuesday night. Bryan Harvey had 16 points and six assists for the Bulldogs (4-3), who shot 63 percent in the second half to take control. Darius Floyd scored 15 points to lead the Rams (1-4), who led 32-27 at halftime before shooting just 9-for-28 (32 percent) after the break. Fresno State took control by going 5-for-7 from 3-point range to start the second half, pushing ahead about 6 minutes in and increasing the margin to 10 in the final seconds.
